<subSubSection id="6EF16510FF80FFADF7FC2710FEF9FA7C" pageId="2" pageNumber="253" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="2654369BFF80FFADF7FC2710FEF9FA7C" blockId="2.[170,1229,1330,1612]" pageId="2" pageNumber="253">
<emphasis id="149FEA89FF80FFADF7FC2710FEA6FADD" bold="true" box="[223,353,1330,1356]" pageId="2" pageNumber="253">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Femora black in basal part (
<figureCitation id="BED02A1EFF80FFADF5962710FD32FADC" box="[693,757,1330,1357]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="2.[166,199,1157,1179]" captionTargetBox="[369,1027,170,1103]" captionTargetId="figure-177@2.[359,1040,164,1126]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Fig. 4–11. C. difficilis. 4 — ♀, habitus, left; 5 — mesonotum, dorsally; 6 — wing (SIZK); 7 — abdomen; 8 — epandrium; 9 — glans; 10 — aculeus, ventrally; 11 — same, apex, enlarged (SMNC)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6452428" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6452428/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="253">fig. 4</figureCitation>
). Wing pattern reticulated, Cell br with 3 hyaline rounded spots; Stigma with one hyaline spot (
<figureCitation id="BED02A1EFF80FFADF4602770FC44FAFC" box="[835,899,1362,1389]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="2.[166,199,1157,1179]" captionTargetBox="[369,1027,170,1103]" captionTargetId="figure-177@2.[359,1040,164,1126]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Fig. 4–11. C. difficilis. 4 — ♀, habitus, left; 5 — mesonotum, dorsally; 6 — wing (SIZK); 7 — abdomen; 8 — epandrium; 9 — glans; 10 — aculeus, ventrally; 11 — same, apex, enlarged (SMNC)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6452428" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6452428/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="253">fig. 6</figureCitation>
). Posterior notopleural seta black, mesonotum sometimes with brownish longitudinal bands (
<figureCitation id="BED02A1EFF80FFADF4FE2750FB87FA1C" box="[989,1088,1394,1421]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="2.[166,199,1157,1179]" captionTargetBox="[369,1027,170,1103]" captionTargetId="figure-177@2.[359,1040,164,1126]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Fig. 4–11. C. difficilis. 4 — ♀, habitus, left; 5 — mesonotum, dorsally; 6 — wing (SIZK); 7 — abdomen; 8 — epandrium; 9 — glans; 10 — aculeus, ventrally; 11 — same, apex, enlarged (SMNC)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6452428" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6452428/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="253">fig. 4–5</figureCitation>
). Oviscape, as long as 3 preceding abdominal tergites (
<figureCitation id="BED02A1EFF80FFADF58F27B0FD2AFA3C" box="[684,749,1426,1453]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="2.[166,199,1157,1179]" captionTargetBox="[369,1027,170,1103]" captionTargetId="figure-177@2.[359,1040,164,1126]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Fig. 4–11. C. difficilis. 4 — ♀, habitus, left; 5 — mesonotum, dorsally; 6 — wing (SIZK); 7 — abdomen; 8 — epandrium; 9 — glans; 10 — aculeus, ventrally; 11 — same, apex, enlarged (SMNC)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6452428" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6452428/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="253">fig. 7</figureCitation>
). Epandriun as in 
<figureCitation id="BED02A1EFF80FFADF4EE27B0FBCDFA3D" box="[973,1034,1426,1452]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="2.[166,199,1157,1179]" captionTargetBox="[369,1027,170,1103]" captionTargetId="figure-177@2.[359,1040,164,1126]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Fig. 4–11. C. difficilis. 4 — ♀, habitus, left; 5 — mesonotum, dorsally; 6 — wing (SIZK); 7 — abdomen; 8 — epandrium; 9 — glans; 10 — aculeus, ventrally; 11 — same, apex, enlarged (SMNC)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6452428" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6452428/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="253">fig. 8</figureCitation>
. and glans as in 
<figureCitation id="BED02A1EFF80FFADF7892790FF2AFA5D" box="[170,237,1458,1484]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="2.[166,199,1157,1179]" captionTargetBox="[369,1027,170,1103]" captionTargetId="figure-177@2.[359,1040,164,1126]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Fig. 4–11. C. difficilis. 4 — ♀, habitus, left; 5 — mesonotum, dorsally; 6 — wing (SIZK); 7 — abdomen; 8 — epandrium; 9 — glans; 10 — aculeus, ventrally; 11 — same, apex, enlarged (SMNC)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6452428" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6452428/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="253">fig. 9</figureCitation>
. Length of aculeus 6 times as long as wide and with one pair of distinct steps at apex (
<figureCitation id="BED02A1EFF80FFADF79127F0FEF5FA7C" box="[178,306,1490,1517]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="2.[166,199,1157,1179]" captionTargetBox="[369,1027,170,1103]" captionTargetId="figure-177@2.[359,1040,164,1126]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Fig. 4–11. C. difficilis. 4 — ♀, habitus, left; 5 — mesonotum, dorsally; 6 — wing (SIZK); 7 — abdomen; 8 — epandrium; 9 — glans; 10 — aculeus, ventrally; 11 — same, apex, enlarged (SMNC)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6452428" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6452428/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="253">fig. 10–11</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="6EF16510FF80FFADF7FC27D0FEE4F9DD" pageId="2" pageNumber="253" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="2654369BFF80FFADF7FC27D0FEE4F9DD" blockId="2.[170,1229,1330,1612]" pageId="2" pageNumber="253">
<emphasis id="149FEA89FF80FFADF7FC27D0FEA9F99D" bold="true" box="[223,366,1522,1548]" pageId="2" pageNumber="253">Comments.</emphasis>
This species is restricted to Northern Europe and mountain areas, and local in 
<collectingCountry id="5EFC760BFF80FFADF62A2431FEF9F9BC" box="[265,318,1555,1581]" name="Iran" pageId="2" pageNumber="253">Iran</collectingCountry>
. Larvae feed in flower heads of dandelions (
<taxonomicName id="E1EB4D18FF80FFADF4692431FC16F9BD" box="[842,977,1555,1580]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Taraxacum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="2" pageNumber="253" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="149FEA89FF80FFADF4692431FC16F9BD" box="[842,977,1555,1580]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="253">Taraxacum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). Host plants in 
<collectingCountry id="5EFC760BFF80FFADF3B82431FB0AF9BC" box="[1179,1229,1555,1581]" name="Iran" pageId="2" pageNumber="253">Iran</collectingCountry>
unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
